709121f-a.title: Manhattan: 5th Avenue - 68th Street
709121f-a.text:
Fifth Ave., east side, south from and including East 68th Street,
showing at the S.E. corner of that point a vacant lot upon which
stood the home of the late Charles T. Yerkes. Occupying the balance
of that block front are the homes of Thomas Fortune Ryan (No. 858),
and Alice G. Vanderbilt (No. 1 East 67th Street). The apartment house
opposite the latter is No. 856 Fifth Ave. and stands upon the site of
the former Judge Elbert H. Gary home. Returning to the foreground one
sees partially at the left, the H. P. Whitney home, No. 1 East 68th
Street.
July 21, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
